      "heading": "No. 3 - '25th Hour'",
      "note": "the mystery pick",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "25th Hour",
          "year": 2002,
          "note": "Spike Lee's adaptation of David Benioff's novel, tracking Edward Norton's Monty Brogan through his last day before a seven-year prison sentence. Made during and after 9/11, not about the attack but surrounded by it. Sean and Amanda single out the mirror 'fuck you' monologue and the imagined-escape ending as two of the century's great scenes; it was originally No. 2 before Sean's late crisis of confidence dropped it to No. 3."
        }
      ]
